var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Contributing-to-DocumenterTypst.jl","page":"Contributing","text":"Thank you for your interest in contributing to DocumenterTypst.jl!","title":"Contributing to DocumenterTypst.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Code-of-Conduct","page":"Contributing","text":"This project follows the Julia Community Standards.","title":"Code of Conduct"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Getting-Started","page":"Contributing","text":"","title":"Getting Started"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Setting-Up-Your-Development-Environment","page":"Contributing","text":"Fork and clone the repository:\ngit clone https://github.com/lucifer1004/DocumenterTypst.jl\ncd DocumenterTypst.jl\nInstall dependencies:\nusing Pkg\nPkg.activate(\".\")\nPkg.instantiate()\nRun tests:\nPkg.test()","title":"Setting Up Your Development Environment"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Making-Changes","page":"Contributing","text":"","title":"Making Changes"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Workflow","page":"Contributing","text":"Create a new branch for your changes:\ngit checkout -b your-feature-branch\nMake your changes and commit them with clear messages:\ngit commit -m \"Add feature X\"\nPush to your fork and create a pull request:\ngit push origin your-feature-branch","title":"Workflow"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Code-Style","page":"Contributing","text":"We use:\n\nRunic.jl for Julia code formatting\nmarkdownlint-cli2 for Markdown linting\n\nFormat your code before committing:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(\"Runic\")\nusing Runic\nRunic.main([\"--verbose\", \".\"])\n\nOr use the justfile (formats both Julia and Markdown):\n\njust format\n\nThis command will:\n\nFormat Julia code with Runic\nLint and auto-fix Markdown files with markdownlint-cli2\n\nCI will check formatting automatically using Runic v1.2 and markdownlint-cli2.","title":"Code Style"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Testing","page":"Contributing","text":"","title":"Testing"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Running-Tests","page":"Contributing","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.test(\"DocumenterTypst\")\n\nOr with just:\n\njust test","title":"Running Tests"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Typst-Backend-Tests","page":"Contributing","text":"Test the Typst backend with different platforms:\n\n# Using just (recommended)\njust test-backend           # Typst_jll (default)\njust test-backend native    # System typst\njust test-backend none      # Only .typ generation (fastest)\n\n# Manual run\nTYPST_PLATFORM=typst julia --project=test/integration test/integration/runtests.jl\n\nAvailable platforms:\n\ntypst (default): Uses Typst_jll.jl, automatic cross-platform\nnative: Uses system-installed typst command\nnone: Only generates .typ files, no PDF compilation (fastest, recommended for development)","title":"Typst Backend Tests"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Adding-Tests","page":"Contributing","text":"When adding new features:\n\nAdd unit tests to test/runtests.jl\nTest both success and error cases\nEnsure tests are fast (use platform=\"none\" to skip compilation)\n\nExample:\n\n@testset \"New Feature\" begin\n    output = render_to_typst(\"**new syntax**\")\n    @test contains(output, \"expected output\")\nend","title":"Adding Tests"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Test-Coverage","page":"Contributing","text":"We aim for 90%+ code coverage. Check coverage locally:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.test(\"DocumenterTypst\"; coverage=true)","title":"Test Coverage"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Documentation","page":"Contributing","text":"","title":"Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Building-Documentation-Locally","page":"Contributing","text":"# HTML documentation\njust docs\n\n# Or manually\njulia --project=docs -e '\n  using Pkg\n  Pkg.develop(PackageSpec(path=pwd()))\n  Pkg.instantiate()\n  include(\"docs/make.jl\")\n'\n\n# Typst/PDF documentation with different platforms\njust docs-typst           # Use Typst_jll (default)\njust docs-typst native    # Use system typst\njust docs-typst none      # Generate .typ source only (fastest for preview)\n\nHTML output will be in docs/build/, Typst/PDF output in docs/build-typst/.","title":"Building Documentation Locally"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Documentation-Style","page":"Contributing","text":"Use clear, concise language\nProvide code examples\nInclude \"See also\" links\nTest all code examples","title":"Documentation Style"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Changelog","page":"Contributing","text":"All user-visible changes must have a changelog entry.","title":"Changelog"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Adding-a-Changelog-Entry","page":"Contributing","text":"Edit CHANGELOG.md under the \"Unreleased\" section:\n\n## Unreleased\n\n### Added\n\n- New feature description. ([#123])\n\n### Fixed\n\n- Bug fix description. ([#124])","title":"Adding a Changelog Entry"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Categories","page":"Contributing","text":"Added: New features\nChanged: Changes in existing functionality\nDeprecated: Soon-to-be removed features\nRemoved: Removed features\nFixed: Bug fixes\nSecurity: Security improvements","title":"Categories"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Linking-Issues/PRs","page":"Contributing","text":"Reference issues and PRs using ([#123]) notation. The link will be auto-generated.","title":"Linking Issues/PRs"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Skip-Changelog","page":"Contributing","text":"For trivial changes (typo fixes, CI tweaks), add the Skip Changelog label to your PR.","title":"Skip Changelog"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Pull-Request-Guidelines","page":"Contributing","text":"","title":"Pull Request Guidelines"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Before-Submitting","page":"Contributing","text":"[ ] Code is formatted (just format or Runic.jl)\n[ ] Tests pass locally (Pkg.test())\n[ ] Typst backend tests pass (if applicable)\n[ ] Spell check passes (typos)\n[ ] Changelog updated (if needed)\n[ ] Documentation updated (if adding features)\n[ ] Commit messages are clear","title":"Before Submitting"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#CI-Checks","page":"Contributing","text":"Your PR will be automatically checked for:\n\n✅ Julia code formatting (Runic)\n✅ Spell checking (Typos)\n✅ File formatting (Prettier)\n✅ Changelog update\n✅ Tests on Linux/macOS/Windows\n✅ Typst backend tests\n✅ Documentation build\n✅ Link checking\n✅ Code coverage\n\nAll checks must pass before merging.","title":"CI Checks"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#PR-Description","page":"Contributing","text":"Include:\n\nWhat: What does this PR do?\nWhy: Why is this change needed?\nHow: How does it work?\nTesting: How was it tested?\n\nExample:\n\n## What\n\nAdds support for custom fonts in Typst output.\n\n## Why\n\nUsers want to match their organization's branding.\n\n## How\n\n- Adds `fonts` parameter to `Typst` constructor\n- Passes `--font-path` to Typst compiler\n- Updates documentation and tests\n\n## Testing\n\n- Added unit tests for font path generation\n- Tested with custom font on Linux/macOS/Windows\n- Updated docs with example\n\nCloses #42","title":"PR Description"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Review-Process","page":"Contributing","text":"Automated CI checks must pass\nAt least one maintainer approval required\nNo unresolved review comments\nUp-to-date with main branch","title":"Review Process"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Issue-Guidelines","page":"Contributing","text":"","title":"Issue Guidelines"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Before-Opening-an-Issue","page":"Contributing","text":"Search existing issues - Your issue may already exist\nCheck documentation - The answer might be there\nTry latest version - The bug might be fixed","title":"Before Opening an Issue"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Bug-Reports","page":"Contributing","text":"Include:\n\nSummary: Brief description\nSteps to reproduce: Minimal reproducible example\nExpected behavior: What should happen\nActual behavior: What actually happens\nEnvironment:\nJulia version:\nDocumenterTypst version:\nOS:\nMinimal example: Complete code to reproduce","title":"Bug Reports"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Feature-Requests","page":"Contributing","text":"Include:\n\nUse case: Why is this needed?\nProposed solution: How should it work?\nAlternatives considered: Other approaches?\nExamples: Code examples of desired API","title":"Feature Requests"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Development-Tips","page":"Contributing","text":"","title":"Development Tips"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Quick-Iteration","page":"Contributing","text":"For fast development cycles, generate only .typ source without compilation:\n\n# Using just\njust docs-typst none\n\n# Or manually\njulia --project=docs docs/make.jl typst none\n\nThen compile manually when needed:\n\ncd docs/build-typst\ntypst compile YourPackage.typ","title":"Quick Iteration"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Debugging","page":"Contributing","text":"Enable debug output:\n\nexport DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"debug-output\"\nexport DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE=\"true\"\njulia docs/make.jl\n\nCheck generated files in debug-output/.","title":"Debugging"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Testing-Against-Documenter-Main","page":"Contributing","text":"Test compatibility with Documenter development version:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(name=\"Documenter\", rev=\"main\")\nPkg.test(\"DocumenterTypst\")","title":"Testing Against Documenter Main"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Release-Process","page":"Contributing","text":"(For maintainers)\n\nUpdate CHANGELOG.md:\nMove \"Unreleased\" to \"Version [vX.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD\"\nAdd version comparison link\nCreate new \"Unreleased\" section\nUpdate Project.toml version\nCommit and tag:\ngit commit -am \"Release vX.Y.Z\"\ngit tag vX.Y.Z\ngit push origin main --tags\nRegister with JuliaRegistrator:\n@JuliaRegistrator register\nGitHub Actions will automatically:\nRun full test suite\nBuild documentation\nCreate GitHub release","title":"Release Process"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Getting-Help","page":"Contributing","text":"Questions: Open a Discussion\nBugs: Open an Issue\nChat: Join Julia Slack #documentation channel","title":"Getting Help"},{"category":"section","location":"contributing/#Recognition","page":"Contributing","text":"Contributors will be:\n\nListed in release notes\nAcknowledged in documentation\nAdded to .zenodo.json (if substantial contribution)\n\nThank you for contributing! 🎉","title":"Recognition"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Getting-Started","page":"Getting Started","text":"This guide will get you up and running with DocumenterTypst.jl in under a minute.","title":"Getting Started"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Installation","page":"Getting Started","text":"Add DocumenterTypst to your documentation project:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(\"DocumenterTypst\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Minimal-Example","page":"Getting Started","text":"Create a docs/make.jl file:\n\nusing Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\nusing YourPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"YourPackage\",\n    authors = \"Your Name\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\nCreate docs/src/index.md:\n\n# YourPackage\n\nWelcome to the documentation!\n\nRun it:\n\njulia --project=docs docs/make.jl\n\nOutput: docs/build/YourPackage.pdf\n\nThat's it! You now have a PDF version of your documentation.","title":"Minimal Example"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Next-Steps","page":"Getting Started","text":"Configuration - Customize compilation, add version numbers, optimize PDF size\nCustom Styling - Change colors, fonts, and layout\nMath Support - Write mathematical equations\nAdvanced Features - Multi-format builds, custom templates, CI/CD\nTroubleshooting - Common issues and solutions","title":"Next Steps"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Common-Scenarios","page":"Getting Started","text":"","title":"Common Scenarios"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Add-a-Version-Number","page":"Getting Started","text":"makedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(version = \"1.0.0\"),\n    ...\n)\n\nOutput: YourPackage-1.0.0.pdf","title":"Add a Version Number"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Multi-Page-Documentation","page":"Getting Started","text":"makedocs(\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"Tutorial\" => \"tutorial.md\",\n        \"API Reference\" => \"api.md\",\n    ],\n    ...\n)","title":"Multi-Page Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Generate-Both-HTML-and-PDF","page":"Getting Started","text":"Build HTML first, then PDF:\n\n# Build HTML\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"YourPackage\",\n    format = Documenter.HTML(),\n    ...\n)\n\n# Build PDF separately\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"YourPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    ...\n)\n\nSee Advanced Features for a complete example.","title":"Generate Both HTML and PDF"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Project-Structure","page":"Getting Started","text":"Typical documentation layout:\n\nYourPackage/\n├── src/\n│   └── YourPackage.jl\n├── docs/\n│   ├── Project.toml          # Documentation dependencies\n│   ├── make.jl               # Build script\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── index.md          # Home page\n│       ├── tutorial.md       # User guide\n│       └── api.md            # API reference\n└── test/\n\nYour docs/Project.toml should include:\n\n[deps]\nDocumenter = \"e30172f5-a6a5-5a46-863b-614d45cd2de4\"\nDocumenterTypst = \"d7fd56dd-41bc-4b2d-b658-79a5840b2e09\"\nYourPackage = \"...\"\n\n[compat]\nDocumenter = \"1.11\"\nDocumenterTypst = \"0.1\"","title":"Project Structure"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/getting_started/#Platform-Options","page":"Getting Started","text":"DocumenterTypst works with three compilation backends:\n\nPlatform Description Use Case\n\"typst\" Uses Typst_jll (default, recommended) Production, CI/CD\n\"native\" Uses system-installed typst executable Development\n\"none\" Generate .typ source only Testing, debugging\n\nDefault configuration (recommended for most users):\n\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst()  # Uses Typst_jll automatically\n\nCustom platform:\n\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"native\")\n\nFor detailed configuration options, see Configuration.","title":"Platform Options"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Math-Support","page":"Math Support","text":"DocumenterTypst supports both native Typst math and LaTeX math syntax.","title":"Math Support"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Which-Should-I-Use?","page":"Math Support","text":"Use Case Recommendation Reason\nNew projects Native Typst math Faster, cleaner, better UX\nMigrating from LaTeX Keep LaTeX math (via mitex) Works as-is, zero migration\nMixed documentation Both (can coexist) Flexibility","title":"Which Should I Use?"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Native-Typst-Math-(Recommended)","page":"Math Support","text":"For new projects, use Typst's native math syntax.","title":"Native Typst Math (Recommended)"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Display-Math","page":"Math Support","text":"```math typst\nsum_(i=1)^n i = (n(n+1))/2\n```\n\nRendered output:\n\nsum_(i=1)^n i = (n(n+1))/2","title":"Display Math"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Complex-Equations","page":"Math Support","text":"```math typst\nintegral_0^infinity e^(-x^2) dif x = sqrt(pi)/2\n```","title":"Complex Equations"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Matrices","page":"Math Support","text":"```math typst\nmat(\n  1, 2, ..., 10;\n  2, 2, ..., 10;\n  dots.v, dots.v, dots.down, dots.v;\n  10, 10, ..., 10;\n)\n```","title":"Matrices"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Advantages","page":"Math Support","text":"Faster compilation: No LaTeX→Typst conversion\nBetter error messages: Typst's errors are clearer\nMore features: Access to Typst-specific functionality\nCleaner syntax: Less verbose than LaTeX","title":"Advantages"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Syntax-Comparison","page":"Math Support","text":"Feature LaTeX Typst\nFractions \\frac{a}{b} a/b or frac(a,b)\nSubscript x_{ij} x_(i j)\nSuperscript x^{2} x^2\nIntegral \\int_a^b integral_a^b\nSum \\sum_{i=1}^n sum_(i=1)^n\nMatrices \\begin{matrix}...\\end{matrix} mat(...)\n\nSee Typst Math Documentation for complete syntax reference.","title":"Syntax Comparison"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#LaTeX-Math-(For-Compatibility)","page":"Math Support","text":"For backward compatibility with existing Documenter documentation, LaTeX math is supported via mitex.","title":"LaTeX Math (For Compatibility)"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Inline-Math","page":"Math Support","text":"The equation `E = mc^2` is Einstein's mass-energy equivalence.\n\nRendered: The equation E = mc^2 is Einstein's mass-energy equivalence.","title":"Inline Math"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Display-Math-2","page":"Math Support","text":"```math\n\\sum_{i=1}^n i = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2}\n```\n\nRendered output:\n\nsum_i=1^n i = fracn(n+1)2","title":"Display Math"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Complex-Equations-2","page":"Math Support","text":"```math\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\nabla \\times \\vec{\\mathbf{B}} -\\, \\frac1c\\, \\frac{\\partial\\vec{\\mathbf{E}}}{\\partial t}\n&= \\frac{4\\pi}{c}\\vec{\\mathbf{j}} \\\\\n\\nabla \\cdot \\vec{\\mathbf{E}} &= 4 \\pi \\rho \\\\\n\\nabla \\times \\vec{\\mathbf{E}}\\, +\\, \\frac1c\\, \\frac{\\partial\\vec{\\mathbf{B}}}{\\partial t}\n&= \\vec{\\mathbf{0}} \\\\\n\\nabla \\cdot \\vec{\\mathbf{B}} &= 0\n\\end{aligned}\n```","title":"Complex Equations"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Supported-Features","page":"Math Support","text":"mitex supports most common LaTeX math commands:\n\nGreek letters: \\alpha, \\beta, \\gamma, ...\nOperators: \\sum, \\prod, \\int, \\lim, ...\nRelations: \\leq, \\geq, \\approx, \\equiv, ...\nBrackets: \\left(, \\right), \\big[, \\Big], ...\nMatrices: \\begin{matrix}, \\begin{pmatrix}, ...\nEnvironments: aligned, cases, array, ...","title":"Supported Features"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Known-Limitations","page":"Math Support","text":"Some advanced LaTeX packages are not supported:\n\nCustom LaTeX packages (tikz, pgfplots, etc.)\nComplex custom macros\nSome AMSmath extensions\n\nWorkaround: Use native Typst math for advanced features.","title":"Known Limitations"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Migration-from-LaTeX","page":"Math Support","text":"","title":"Migration from LaTeX"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Keep-Using-LaTeX-Math","page":"Math Support","text":"Your existing LaTeX math works as-is via mitex:\n\n`\\alpha + \\beta = \\gamma`\n\n```math\n\\frac{\\partial f}{\\partial x} = \\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{f(x+h) - f(x)}{h}\n```\n\nNo changes required!","title":"Keep Using LaTeX Math"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Gradual-Migration-to-Typst","page":"Math Support","text":"Convert incrementally as you update documentation:\n\nLaTeX (old):\n\n```math\n\\sum_{i=1}^n i = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2}\n```\n\nTypst (new):\n\n```math typst\nsum_(i=1)^n i = (n(n+1))/2\n```","title":"Gradual Migration to Typst"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Mixed-Approach","page":"Math Support","text":"You can use both in the same document:\n\nLegacy section with LaTeX: `\\sum_{i=1}^n i`\n\nNew section with Typst:\n\n```math typst\nsum_(i=1)^n i\n```","title":"Mixed Approach"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Best-Practices","page":"Math Support","text":"","title":"Best Practices"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#For-New-Projects","page":"Math Support","text":"Use native Typst math for better performance and cleaner syntax\nLearn Typst syntax - it's simpler and more intuitive than LaTeX\nSee Typst tutorial for examples","title":"For New Projects"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#For-Existing-Projects","page":"Math Support","text":"Keep LaTeX math for zero migration cost\nConvert incrementally as you update sections\nTest changes carefully to ensure rendering is correct","title":"For Existing Projects"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#For-Large-Equations","page":"Math Support","text":"Break complex equations into smaller parts:\n\n// Bad (hard to read)\n$ (a + b + c + d + e + f + g + h + i + j) / (x + y + z) $\n\n// Good (readable)\n$ (a + b + c + d + e + f + g + h + i + j) /\n  (x + y + z) $","title":"For Large Equations"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Debugging-Math","page":"Math Support","text":"","title":"Debugging Math"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Enable-Debug-Output","page":"Math Support","text":"export DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"typst-debug\"\njulia docs/make.jl\n\nCheck typst-debug/*.typ to see how math was converted.","title":"Enable Debug Output"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Common-Issues","page":"Math Support","text":"Issue: Math doesn't render correctly\n\nSolution:\n\nCheck for unsupported LaTeX commands\nTry native Typst syntax instead\nEnable debug output to see converted code\nConsult mitex documentation for supported commands\n\nIssue: Spacing looks wrong\n\nSolution:\n\nLaTeX: Use \\,, \\;, \\quad for manual spacing\nTypst: Use space, h(1em), thin, thick spacing\n\nIssue: Inline math not working\n\nSolution:\n\nUse backticks for inline math: E = mc^2\nNative Typst inline math ($...$) only works in .typ files","title":"Common Issues"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/math/#Resources","page":"Math Support","text":"Typst Math Documentation - Complete math syntax reference\nmitex Documentation - LaTeX compatibility layer\nLaTeX to Typst Guide - Migration guide","title":"Resources"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Troubleshooting","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Common issues and their solutions.","title":"Troubleshooting"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Installation-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"","title":"Installation Issues"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Package-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: ERROR: The following package names could not be resolved: DocumenterTypst\n\nSolution:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.Registry.update()\nPkg.add(\"DocumenterTypst\")","title":"Package Not Found"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Dependency-Conflicts","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: Version conflicts with Documenter\n\nSolution:\n\n# Update to latest compatible versions\nPkg.update([\"Documenter\", \"DocumenterTypst\"])\n\n# Or specify versions explicitly\nPkg.add(name=\"Documenter\", version=\"1.11\")\nPkg.add(\"DocumenterTypst\")","title":"Dependency Conflicts"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Compilation-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"","title":"Compilation Issues"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Typst-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: ERROR: typst command not found\n\nWhen: Using platform=\"native\"\n\nSolution:\n\nUse default platform=\"typst\" (recommended)\nOr install Typst:\n# macOS\nbrew install typst\n\n# Linux\ncargo install --git https://github.com/typst/typst\n\n# Windows\nwinget install Typst.Typst","title":"Typst Not Found"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Compilation-Timeout","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: Build hangs or takes too long\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck for infinite loops in custom templates\nUse platform=\"none\" to test without compilation\nEnable verbose output:\nexport DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE=\"true\"\njulia docs/make.jl","title":"Compilation Timeout"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Content-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"","title":"Content Issues"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Math-Not-Rendering","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: Math equations don't appear or look wrong\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck syntax:\n# Correct (LaTeX)\n\n```math\n\\sum_{i=1}^n i\n```\n\n# Correct (Typst)\n\n```math typst\nsum_(i=1)^n i\n```\nEscape backslashes:\n# Wrong\n\n`\\alpha`\n\n# Correct\n\n`\\\\alpha`\nUse mitex-supported commands - Some advanced LaTeX packages aren't supported","title":"Math Not Rendering"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Images-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: Images don't appear in PDF\n\nSolutions:\n\nUse relative paths:\n# If in docs/src/manual/guide.md\n\n![Caption](../assets/image.png) # ✅\n![Caption](assets/image.png) # ❌\nAvoid absolute URLs - Download images locally instead\nCheck file exists:\nls docs/src/assets/image.png","title":"Images Not Found"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Code-Blocks-Wrong-Language","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: Syntax highlighting incorrect\n\nSolution: Specify language explicitly:\n\n```julia  # Not `jl`\nfunction hello()\nprintln(\"Hello!\")\nend\n\n```\n\n```","title":"Code Blocks Wrong Language"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Cross-References-Broken","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: @ref links don't work\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck anchor exists:\n## My Section # Creates anchor \"My-Section\"\n\nSee [My Section](@ref) # ✅\nSee [My Section](#my-section) # ✅ (lowercase)\nUse exact heading text:\n## Getting Started\n\n[Getting Started](@ref) # ✅\n[Get Started](@ref) # ❌","title":"Cross-References Broken"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Template-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"","title":"Template Issues"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Custom-Template-Not-Loading","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: Changes in custom.typ don't apply\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck file location:\ndocs/src/assets/custom.typ  # ✅\ndocs/assets/custom.typ       # ❌\nVerify syntax:\n#let config = (\n  text-size: 12pt,  # ✅ Comma\n)\nClear cache:\nrm -rf docs/build\njulia docs/make.jl","title":"Custom Template Not Loading"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Fonts-Not-Found","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: Custom fonts don't work\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck font name:\n# Correct\ntext-font: (\"Inter\", \"DejaVu Sans\")\n\n# Wrong (use exact name)\ntext-font: (\"inter\", \"dejavu\")\nInstall font system-wide\nUse font path:\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = `typst --font-path /path/to/fonts`\n)","title":"Fonts Not Found"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#CI/CD-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"","title":"CI/CD Issues"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#GitHub-Actions-Failing","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: CI build fails\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck Julia version:\n- uses: julia-actions/setup-julia@v2\n  with:\n    version: \"1.10\" # Minimum for DocumenterTypst\nInstall dependencies:\n- name: Install dependencies\n  run: |\n    julia --project=docs -e '\n      using Pkg\n      Pkg.develop(PackageSpec(path=pwd()))\n      Pkg.instantiate()'\nAdd secrets:\nDOCUMENTER_KEY: For deployment\nGITHUB_TOKEN: Automatic","title":"GitHub Actions Failing"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Deploy-Failing","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: PDF not deployed to gh-pages\n\nSolution: Use Documenter's deploy system:\n\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(), ...)\n\ndeploydocs(\n    repo = \"github.com/user/Package.jl\",\n    devbranch = \"main\",\n)","title":"Deploy Failing"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Performance-Issues","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"","title":"Performance Issues"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Slow-Builds","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: Compilation takes too long\n\nSolutions:\n\nUse platform=\"none\" for testing:\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\")\nDisable doctests during development:\nmakedocs(doctest = false, ...)\nSplit large documents\nUse incremental compilation (Typst's default)","title":"Slow Builds"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Large-PDF-Files","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Problem: PDF file too large\n\nSolutions:\n\nCompress images before including\nUse vector graphics (SVG/PDF) instead of PNG\nReduce image resolution for screen viewing","title":"Large PDF Files"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Debug-Mode","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"","title":"Debug Mode"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Enable-Comprehensive-Debugging","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"# Save generated .typ files\nexport DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"debug-output\"\n\n# Verbose Documenter output\nexport DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE=\"true\"\n\n# Build\njulia --project=docs docs/make.jl","title":"Enable Comprehensive Debugging"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Inspect-Generated-Files","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"cd debug-output\nls -la  # See all generated files\n\n# Compile manually to see errors\ntypst compile YourPackage.typ","title":"Inspect Generated Files"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Getting-Help","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"If you can't resolve an issue:\n\nCheck existing issues: GitHub Issues\nCreate minimal example:\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MWE\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\"index.md\"],\n)\nInclude debug output:\nJulia version: versioninfo()\nDocumenterTypst version: Pkg.status(\"DocumenterTypst\")\nError messages (full stack trace)\nGenerated .typ file (if relevant)\nOpen an issue: Provide all above information","title":"Getting Help"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Known-Limitations","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"","title":"Known Limitations"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Not-Yet-Supported","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"Live reload during development (use platform=\"none\" + manual compile)\nInteractive elements (PDF format limitation)\nAnimated GIFs (use static frames)\nSome advanced LaTeX packages in math","title":"Not Yet Supported"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Workarounds","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"For unsupported features, consider:\n\nGenerate HTML docs for interactive content\nUse native Typst features instead of LaTeX\nContribute a PR to add support!","title":"Workarounds"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/troubleshooting/#Version-Compatibility","page":"Troubleshooting","text":"DocumenterTypst Documenter Julia\n0.1.x 1.11+ 1.10+\n\nAlways use compatible versions to avoid issues.","title":"Version Compatibility"},{"category":"section","location":"release-notes/#Release-Notes","page":"Release Notes","text":"Pages = [\"release-notes.md\"]\nDepth = 2\n\nThis page documents the release history of DocumenterTypst.jl.\n\nThe format is based on Keep a Changelog, and this project adheres to Semantic Versioning.\n\nFor contributing guidelines, see Contributing.\n\n\n\nnote: Automatic Generation\nThis page is automatically generated from CHANGELOG.md using the Documenter changelog extension. To update it, edit CHANGELOG.md and rebuild the documentation.\n\n\n\n<!– The actual changelog content will be inserted here by Documenter –>","title":"Release Notes"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Configuration","page":"Configuration","text":"Complete configuration reference for DocumenterTypst.","title":"Configuration"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Constructor","page":"Configuration","text":"DocumenterTypst.Typst(;\n    platform = \"typst\",\n    version = \"\",\n    typst = nothing,\n    optimize_pdf = true,\n    use_system_fonts = true,\n    font_paths = String[],\n)","title":"Constructor"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Parameters","page":"Configuration","text":"","title":"Parameters"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#platform::String","page":"Configuration","text":"Compilation backend. Default: \"typst\"\n\nValue Description Use Case\n\"typst\" Uses Typst_jll.jl (recommended) Production, CI/CD\n\"native\" Uses system typst executable Development\n\"none\" Generate .typ source only Testing, debugging\n\nExamples:\n\n# Default (recommended)\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst()\n\n# Use system typst\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"native\")\n\n# Generate source only (fast for development)\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\")\n\nInstalling native Typst:\n\n# macOS\nbrew install typst\n\n# Linux (via cargo)\ncargo install --git https://github.com/typst/typst\n\n# Windows\nwinget install --id Typst.Typst","title":"platform::String"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#version::String","page":"Configuration","text":"Version string for PDF filename. Default: \"\"\n\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(version = \"1.2.3\")\n# Output: MyPackage-1.2.3.pdf\n\nIf unset, no version suffix is added.","title":"version::String"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#typst::Union{Cmd,-String,-Nothing}","page":"Configuration","text":"Custom path to typst executable. Default: nothing\n\nOnly used with platform=\"native\".\n\n# String path\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = \"/opt/typst/bin/typst\"\n)\n\n# Cmd object (with custom flags)\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = `/usr/local/bin/typst --font-path /custom/fonts`\n)","title":"typst::Union{Cmd, String, Nothing}"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#optimize_pdf::Bool","page":"Configuration","text":"Enable automatic PDF optimization. Default: true\n\nWhen enabled, DocumenterTypst uses pdfcpu to compress the generated PDF:\n\nCompresses uncompressed content streams\nOptimizes PDF object structure\nTypically reduces file size by 60-85% for large documents\nAdds ~2 seconds to build time\n\n# Enable optimization (recommended for production)\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(optimize_pdf = true)\n\n# Disable optimization (faster builds for development)\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(optimize_pdf = false)\n\nOutput:\n\nInfo: TypstWriter: optimizing PDF with pdfcpu...\n└   size_before = \"42.79 MB\"\n\nInfo: TypstWriter: PDF optimization completed.\n│   size_after = \"15.23 MB\"\n│   reduction = \"64.4%\"\n└   time = \"1.85s\"","title":"optimize_pdf::Bool"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#use_system_fonts::Bool","page":"Configuration","text":"Control whether Typst can use system-installed fonts. Default: true\n\nWhen set to false, uses Typst's --ignore-system-fonts flag:\n\nPrevents Type 3 emoji fonts (e.g., AppleColorEmoji) from being embedded\nCan reduce PDF size by 40+ MB for emoji-heavy documents\nOnly fonts explicitly specified in the template will be used\n\n# Use system fonts (default, maximum compatibility)\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(use_system_fonts = true)\n\n# Ignore system fonts (recommended for production)\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(use_system_fonts = false)\n\nPerformance comparison (Julia documentation, 2211 pages):\n\nConfiguration PDF Size\nWith system fonts 100 MB\nWithout system fonts 60 MB\n+ optimization 15 MB","title":"use_system_fonts::Bool"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#font_paths::Vector{String}","page":"Configuration","text":"Additional font directories for Typst. Default: String[]\n\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    font_paths = [\"/path/to/fonts\", \"/another/path\"]\n)\n\nFonts in these directories will be available for use in custom templates.","title":"font_paths::Vector{String}"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Documenter-Integration","page":"Configuration","text":"DocumenterTypst respects these makedocs arguments:","title":"Documenter Integration"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#sitename::String","page":"Configuration","text":"Document title. Appears on title page and in PDF metadata.\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage Documentation\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n)","title":"sitename::String"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#authors::String","page":"Configuration","text":"Author names. Appears on title page.\n\nmakedocs(\n    authors = \"John Doe, Jane Smith\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n)","title":"authors::String"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#pages::Vector","page":"Configuration","text":"Document structure. Converted to table of contents and sections.\n\nmakedocs(\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"Manual\" => [\n            \"Getting Started\" => \"manual/start.md\",\n            \"Advanced\" => \"manual/advanced.md\",\n        ],\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ],\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n)","title":"pages::Vector"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Production-Configuration","page":"Configuration","text":"","title":"Production Configuration"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Recommended-Settings","page":"Configuration","text":"For minimal PDF size and optimal quality:\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n        platform = \"typst\",           # Use Typst_jll (default)\n        optimize_pdf = true,          # Enable optimization (default)\n        use_system_fonts = false,     # Minimize size (NOT default)\n    ),\n)\n\nThis configuration produces PDFs that are:\n\n85% smaller than unoptimized builds\n40-60 MB smaller than builds with system fonts\nComparable in size to LaTeX output","title":"Recommended Settings"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Development-Configuration","page":"Configuration","text":"For fast iteration during development:\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n        platform = \"none\",            # Skip PDF generation\n        optimize_pdf = false,         # Skip optimization\n    ),\n    doctest = false,                  # Skip doctests\n)\n\nThis only generates the .typ source file (~1 second for large projects).","title":"Development Configuration"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Environment-Variables","page":"Configuration","text":"","title":"Environment Variables"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG","page":"Configuration","text":"Save generated .typ files for debugging.\n\n# Save to default temp directory\nexport DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"\"\n\n# Save to specific directory\nexport DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=\"typst-debug\"\n\njulia docs/make.jl\n\nOutput location will be printed:\n\n┌ Info: Typst sources copied for debugging to /path/to/typst-debug","title":"DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE","page":"Configuration","text":"Enable verbose output from Documenter.\n\nexport DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE=\"true\"\njulia docs/make.jl","title":"DOCUMENTER_VERBOSE"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Custom-Templates","page":"Configuration","text":"Override default styling by creating docs/src/assets/custom.typ:\n\n// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n// Custom colors and fonts\n#let config = (\n  light-blue: rgb(\"3498db\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"2c3e50\"),\n\n  // Custom font sizes\n  text-size: 12pt,\n  code-size: 10pt,\n\n  // Custom fonts\n  text-font: (\"Times New Roman\", \"DejaVu Serif\"),\n  code-font: (\"Fira Code\", \"DejaVu Sans Mono\"),\n)\n\nThe content of this file is automatically embedded in the generated document.\n\nSee Custom Styling for detailed examples.","title":"Custom Templates"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Custom-Title-Pages","page":"Configuration","text":"Replace the default title page:\n\n// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n#let config = (\n  skip-default-titlepage: true,  // Skip the default title page\n  // ... other config options\n)\n\n// Your custom title page\n#page(\n  margin: (left: 2cm, right: 2cm, bottom: 3cm, top: 2cm),\n  header: none,\n  footer: none,\n  numbering: none,\n)[\n  #align(center)[\n    #v(3cm)\n    #image(\"logo.png\", width: 150pt)\n    #v(2cm)\n    #text(size: 48pt, weight: \"bold\")[My Package]\n    #v(1cm)\n    #text(size: 24pt)[Documentation]\n    #v(1fr)\n    #text(size: 14pt, fill: gray)[Version 1.0 • December 2025]\n  ]\n]\n\n#pagebreak()","title":"Custom Title Pages"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Performance-Tuning","page":"Configuration","text":"","title":"Performance Tuning"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Build-Timing","page":"Configuration","text":"DocumenterTypst reports detailed timing for each build stage:\n\nInfo: TypstWriter: AST conversion completed.\n└   time = \"0.45s\"\n\nInfo: TypstWriter: Typst compilation completed.\n└   time = \"0.33s\"\n\nInfo: TypstWriter: PDF optimization completed.\n│   size_after = \"0.04 MB\"\n│   reduction = \"34.9%\"\n└   time = \"0.05s\"\n\nTotal build time is typically under 10 seconds for medium-sized documentation.","title":"Build Timing"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Parallel-Builds","page":"Configuration","text":"DocumenterTypst uses temporary directories, so you can run multiple builds in parallel:\n\njulia --project=docs -e 'include(\"docs/make.jl\")' &\njulia --project=docs -e 'include(\"docs/make_alternate.jl\")' &\nwait","title":"Parallel Builds"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#CI/CD-Integration","page":"Configuration","text":"","title":"CI/CD Integration"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#GitHub-Actions","page":"Configuration","text":"- name: Build PDF documentation\n  run: |\n    julia --project=docs -e '\n      using Pkg\n      Pkg.develop(PackageSpec(path=pwd()))\n      Pkg.instantiate()\n      include(\"docs/make.jl\")\n    '\n  env:\n    DOCUMENTER_KEY: ${{ secrets.DOCUMENTER_KEY }}","title":"GitHub Actions"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Platform-Support","page":"Configuration","text":"Linux: Works out of the box with Typst_jll.\n\nmacOS: Works out of the box with Typst_jll.\n\nWindows: Works out of the box with Typst_jll. Path handling is automatically normalized.","title":"Platform Support"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Advanced-Usage","page":"Configuration","text":"","title":"Advanced Usage"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Pure-Typst-Files","page":"Configuration","text":"Include existing .typ files directly alongside Markdown files:\n\nmakedocs(\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",           # Markdown (converted)\n        \"Manual\" => \"manual.typ\",       # Pure Typst (included as-is)\n        \"API\" => [\n            \"Overview\" => \"api/index.md\",\n            \"Reference\" => \"api/ref.typ\",\n        ],\n    ]\n)\n\nHow it works:\n\nHeading levels: Automatically adjusted using Typst's offset parameter\nResource paths: Preserved via #include\nPage breaks: Level 1-2 headings get automatic page breaks\n\nLimitations:\n\nContent is only included in Typst/PDF output, not HTML\nDocumenter's cross-reference system doesn't index .typ content","title":"Pure Typst Files"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Documenter-Directives-in-Typst-Files","page":"Configuration","text":"tip: New in v0.2.0\nYou can now use Documenter-style directives within .typ files!\n\nWhile .typ files are not processed through Documenter's full pipeline, you can use special preprocessing directives to access Documenter features:","title":"Documenter Directives in Typst Files"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#@typst-docs-Include-API-Documentation","page":"Configuration","text":"= API Reference\n\n// @typst-docs MyModule.function_name\n// @typst-docs MyModule.AnotherType\n\nThis will expand to the full docstring documentation, similar to @docs blocks in Markdown files.\n\nExample output:\n\n#raw(\"MyModule.function_name\") #label(...) -- Function.\n#extended_grid(columns: (2em, 1fr), [], [\n  // Formatted docstring content with code blocks, lists, etc.\n])","title":"@typst-docs - Include API Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#@typst-example-Execute-and-Display-Code","page":"Configuration","text":"= Examples\n\n// @typst-example\n// x = 1 + 1\n// println(\"Result: $x\")\n// @typst-example-end\n\nThis executes the Julia code and displays both the code and its output, similar to @example blocks in Markdown.\n\nGenerated output:\n\n#raw(\"x = 1 + 1\\nprintln(\\\"Result: \\$x\\\")\", block: true, lang: \"julia\")\n#raw(\"Result: 2\", block: true, lang: \"text\")","title":"@typst-example - Execute and Display Code"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#@typst-ref-Cross-Reference-Links","page":"Configuration","text":"See also: // @typst-ref MyModule.related_function\n\nThis generates a clickable cross-reference link, similar to @ref in Markdown.\n\nGenerated output:\n\nSee also: #link(label(\"file.typ#MyModule.related_function\"))[MyModule.related_function]","title":"@typst-ref - Cross-Reference Links"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#How-It-Works","page":"Configuration","text":"Preprocessing: When a .typ file is included, DocumenterTypst scans for these special comments\nExpansion: Each directive is expanded into native Typst code\n\nLimitations:\n\nDirectives must be in comments starting with //\n@typst-example code runs in the module's namespace (use fully qualified names if needed)\nCross-references only work within the Typst/PDF output\n\nSee Getting Started for a complete example.","title":"How It Works"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/configuration/#Troubleshooting","page":"Configuration","text":"See Troubleshooting Guide for common issues and solutions.","title":"Troubleshooting"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Custom-Styling","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Customize the appearance of your PDF documentation.","title":"Custom Styling"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Overview","page":"Custom Styling","text":"DocumenterTypst uses a default template (documenter.typ) that provides professional styling out of the box. You can customize it by creating your own custom.typ file.","title":"Overview"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Quick-Start","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Create docs/src/assets/custom.typ:\n\n// Override default configuration\n#let config = (\n  // Your customizations here\n  light-blue: rgb(\"3498db\"),\n  text-size: 12pt,\n)\n\nThis file is automatically loaded if it exists.","title":"Quick Start"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Available-Options","page":"Custom Styling","text":"","title":"Available Options"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Colors","page":"Custom Styling","text":"#let config = (\n  // Primary colors\n  light-blue: rgb(\"6b85dd\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"4266d5\"),\n  light-red: rgb(\"d66661\"),\n  dark-red: rgb(\"c93d39\"),\n  light-green: rgb(\"6bab5b\"),\n  dark-green: rgb(\"3b972e\"),\n  light-purple: rgb(\"aa7dc0\"),\n  dark-purple: rgb(\"945bb0\"),\n\n  // UI colors\n  codeblock-background: rgb(\"f6f6f6\"),\n  codeblock-border: rgb(\"e6e6e6\"),\n\n  // Admonition colors\n  admonition-colors: (\n    default: rgb(\"363636\"),\n    danger: rgb(\"da0b00\"),\n    warning: rgb(\"ffdd57\"),\n    note: rgb(\"209cee\"),\n    info: rgb(\"209cee\"),\n    tip: rgb(\"22c35b\"),\n    compat: rgb(\"1db5c9\"),\n  ),\n)","title":"Colors"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Typography","page":"Custom Styling","text":"#let config = (\n  // Font sizes\n  text-size: 11pt,\n  code-size: 9pt,\n  heading-size-title: 24pt,\n  heading-size-part: 18pt,\n  heading-size-chapter: 18pt,\n  heading-size-section: 14pt,\n  heading-size-subsection: 13pt,\n  heading-size-subsubsection: 12pt,\n\n  // Font families\n  // Default fonts (embedded in Typst packages for cross-platform consistency):\n  // - Libertinus Serif (text)\n  // - DejaVu Sans Mono (code)\n  // You can override with system fonts or custom fonts:\n  text-font: (\"Inter\", \"DejaVu Sans\"),\n  code-font: (\"JetBrains Mono\", \"DejaVu Sans Mono\"),\n)","title":"Typography"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Layout","page":"Custom Styling","text":"#let config = (\n  // Table styling\n  table-stroke-width: 0.5pt,\n  table-stroke-color: rgb(\"cccccc\"),\n  table-inset: 8pt,\n\n  // Quote styling\n  quote-background: rgb(\"f8f8f8\"),\n  quote-border-color: rgb(\"cccccc\"),\n  quote-border-width: 4pt,\n  quote-inset: (left: 15pt, right: 15pt, top: 10pt, bottom: 10pt),\n\n  // Admonition styling\n  admonition-title-inset: (left: 1em, right: 5pt, top: 5pt, bottom: 5pt),\n  admonition-content-inset: 10pt,\n)","title":"Layout"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Code-Block-Customization","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Control how code blocks are rendered:\n\n#let config = (\n  // Engine selection: \"codly\" (default), \"builtin\", or \"custom\"\n  codeblock-engine: \"codly\",\n\n  // For custom engine\n  codeblock-custom-show: none,       // Function: (raw) => { ... }\n\n  // Codly configuration dictionary (only used when codeblock-engine: \"codly\")\n  // All parameters are optional; defaults are provided for common options\n  // Users can add ANY codly parameter here\n  codly-options: (\n    // Examples of parameters you can set:\n    // languages: codly-languages,   // Language definitions\n    // number-format: num => [...],  // Line number formatting\n    // zebra-fill: luma(250),        // Alternate row backgrounds\n    // fill: rgb(\"f6f6f6\"),          // Background color\n    // stroke: 1pt + rgb(\"e6e6e6\"),  // Border\n    // ... any other codly parameter\n  ),\n)\n\nDefault values (automatically applied if not specified):\n\nlanguages: codly-languages (all built-in languages)\nnumber-format: none (no line numbers)\nzebra-fill: none (no zebra stripes)\nfill: cfg.codeblock-background (uses color config)\nstroke: 1pt + cfg.codeblock-border (uses color config)\n\nEnable line numbers and zebra stripes:\n\n#let config = (\n  codly-options: (\n    number-format: num => text(fill: gray)[#num],\n    zebra-fill: luma(250),\n  ),\n)\n\nAdvanced: Override multiple parameters:\n\n#let config = (\n  codly-options: (\n    languages: my-custom-langs,  // Custom language definitions\n    number-format: num => text(fill: blue)[#num],\n    zebra-fill: rgb(\"f0f8f8\"),\n    fill: rgb(\"fafafa\"),\n    stroke: 2pt + rgb(\"4a9eff\"),\n    // You can add ANY codly parameter here, not just the common ones\n    display-name: true,\n    display-icon: false,\n    // ... etc\n  ),\n)\n\nwarning: Important\nWhen using codeblock-engine: \"codly\", do not manually call show: codly-init.with() or codly(...) in your custom.typ file. All codly configuration should be done through the codly-options dictionary to avoid conflicts.\n\nUsing builtin Typst rendering:\n\n#let config = (\n  codeblock-engine: \"builtin\",\n  codeblock-background: rgb(\"f0f0f0\"),\n  codeblock-border: rgb(\"d0d0d0\"),\n)\n\nCustom code block renderer:\n\n#let my-code-renderer(it) = {\n  if it.block {\n    // Block code: fancy styling\n    block(\n      width: 100%,\n      fill: gradient.linear(rgb(\"e8f4f8\"), rgb(\"f0f8ff\")),\n      stroke: 2pt + rgb(\"4a9eff\"),\n      inset: 12pt,\n      radius: 5pt,\n      breakable: true,\n    )[\n      #if it.lang != none {\n        text(weight: \"bold\", fill: rgb(\"4a9eff\"))[#it.lang]\n        linebreak()\n      }\n      #it\n    ]\n  } else {\n    // Inline code: simple box\n    box(\n      fill: rgb(\"f5f5f5\"),\n      inset: (x: 3pt, y: 1pt),\n      radius: 2pt,\n    )[#it]\n  }\n}\n\n#let config = (\n  codeblock-engine: \"custom\",\n  codeblock-custom-show: my-code-renderer,\n)","title":"Code Block Customization"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Header-Customization","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Control page headers:\n\n#let config = (\n  // Mode: \"chapter\" (default), \"none\", or \"custom\"\n  header-mode: \"chapter\",\n\n  // Font size for default header\n  header-size: 10pt,\n\n  // Alignment for default header\n  header-alignment: right,       // left, center, or right\n\n  // Line stroke below header\n  header-line-stroke: 0.5pt,\n\n  // For custom mode\n  header-custom-function: none,  // Function: (loc, cfg) => { ... }\n)\n\nDisable headers:\n\n#let config = (\n  header-mode: \"none\",\n)\n\nLeft-aligned chapter headers:\n\n#let config = (\n  header-alignment: left,  // Change from default 'right'\n)\n\nCustom header function:\n\n#let my-header(loc, cfg) = {\n  if loc.page() <= 1 { return }\n\n  align(right)[\n    #text(10pt, fill: gray)[\n      My Documentation · Page #loc.page()\n    ]\n  ]\n  line(length: 100%, stroke: 0.5pt + gray)\n}\n\n#let config = (\n  header-mode: \"custom\",\n  header-custom-function: my-header,\n)","title":"Header Customization"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Footer-Customization","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Control page footers:\n\n#let config = (\n  // Mode: \"page-number\" (default), \"none\", or \"custom\"\n  footer-mode: \"page-number\",\n\n  // Font size for default footer\n  footer-size: 10pt,\n\n  // Alignment for default footer\n  footer-alignment: center,  // left, center, or right\n\n  // Show footer on part pages?\n  footer-show-on-part-pages: false,\n\n  // For custom mode\n  footer-custom-function: none,  // Function: (loc, cfg) => { ... }\n)\n\nRight-aligned page numbers:\n\n#let config = (\n  footer-alignment: right,\n)\n\nCustom footer with copyright:\n\n#let my-footer(loc, cfg) = {\n  if loc.page() <= 1 { return }\n\n  // Skip part pages\n  let parts_on_page = query(heading.where(level: 1)).filter(h => h.location().page() == loc.page())\n  if parts_on_page.len() > 0 { return }\n\n  grid(\n    columns: (1fr, auto, 1fr),\n    align: (left, center, right),\n    text(9pt, fill: gray)[© 2025 My Company],\n    text(11pt)[#counter(page).display()],\n    text(9pt, fill: gray)[Internal Documentation],\n  )\n}\n\n#let config = (\n  footer-mode: \"custom\",\n  footer-custom-function: my-footer,\n)","title":"Footer Customization"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Page-Numbering-Customization","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Control page number format:\n\n#let config = (\n  // Format for frontmatter (title page, TOC)\n  page-numbering-frontmatter: \"i\",  // Roman numerals\n\n  // Format for main content\n  page-numbering-mainmatter: \"1\",   // Arabic numerals\n\n  // Custom numbering function (overrides both above)\n  page-numbering-custom: none,      // Function: (nums, cfg) => { ... }\n)\n\nDifferent numbering formats:\n\n#let config = (\n  page-numbering-frontmatter: \"I\",    // Roman uppercase\n  page-numbering-mainmatter: \"1 / 1\", // Page X of Y format\n)\n\nChinese page numbering:\n\n#let chinese-page-number(nums, cfg) = {\n  let page-num = nums.first()\n  [第 #page-num 页]  // \"Page N\" in Chinese\n}\n\n#let config = (\n  page-numbering-custom: chinese-page-number,\n)\n\nComplex page numbering:\n\n#let fancy-numbering(nums, cfg) = {\n  let page-num = nums.first()\n  // Add prefix based on context\n  context {\n    let loc = here()\n    let chapters = query(heading.where(level: 2))\n\n    // Find current chapter\n    let ch-num = 0\n    for ch in chapters {\n      if ch.location().page() <= loc.page() {\n        ch-num = ch-num + 1\n      }\n    }\n\n    if ch-num > 0 {\n      [Ch.#ch-num-#page-num]\n    } else {\n      [#page-num]\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n#let config = (\n  page-numbering-custom: fancy-numbering,\n)","title":"Page Numbering Customization"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Example-Customizations","page":"Custom Styling","text":"","title":"Example Customizations"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Complete-Example:-Enterprise-Style","page":"Custom Styling","text":"// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n// Custom header showing chapter info\n#let my-header(loc, cfg) = {\n  if loc.page() <= 1 { return }\n\n  let parts_on_page = query(heading.where(level: 1)).filter(h => h.location().page() == loc.page())\n  if parts_on_page.len() > 0 { return }\n\n  let chapters_on_page = query(heading.where(level: 2)).filter(h => h.location().page() == loc.page())\n  if chapters_on_page.len() > 0 { return }\n\n  // Find current chapter\n  let all_chapters = query(heading.where(level: 2))\n  let current_chapter = none\n  for ch in all_chapters {\n    if ch.location().page() <= loc.page() {\n      current_chapter = ch\n    } else {\n      break\n    }\n  }\n\n  if current_chapter != none {\n    grid(\n      columns: (1fr, auto),\n      align: (left, right),\n      text(10pt, fill: cfg.dark-blue)[#current_chapter.body],\n      text(10pt, fill: gray)[Page #loc.page()],\n    )\n    line(length: 100%, stroke: 0.5pt + cfg.dark-blue)\n  }\n}\n\n// Custom footer\n#let my-footer(loc, cfg) = {\n  if loc.page() <= 1 { return }\n\n  let parts_on_page = query(heading.where(level: 1)).filter(h => h.location().page() == loc.page())\n  if parts_on_page.len() > 0 { return }\n\n  align(center)[\n    #text(10pt)[#counter(page).display()]\n  ]\n}\n\n#let config = (\n  // Code blocks with line numbers\n  codly-options: (\n    number-format: num => text(fill: gray)[#num],\n  ),\n\n  // Custom header and footer\n  header-mode: \"custom\",\n  header-custom-function: my-header,\n  footer-mode: \"custom\",\n  footer-custom-function: my-footer,\n\n  // Custom colors\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"2e5cb8\"),\n  light-blue: rgb(\"5a8dd6\"),\n\n  // Larger text\n  text-size: 12pt,\n  code-size: 10pt,\n)","title":"Complete Example: Enterprise Style"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Modern-Dark-Theme","page":"Custom Styling","text":"#let config = (\n  light-blue: rgb(\"61afef\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"528bff\"),\n  codeblock-background: rgb(\"282c34\"),\n  text-font: (\"SF Pro Display\", \"Inter\", \"DejaVu Sans\"),\n  text-size: 11pt,\n  codly-options: (\n    number-format: num => text(fill: gray)[#num],\n  ),\n)","title":"Modern Dark Theme"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Academic-Style","page":"Custom Styling","text":"#let config = (\n  text-font: (\"Times New Roman\", \"Liberation Serif\"),\n  code-font: (\"Courier New\", \"Liberation Mono\"),\n  text-size: 12pt,\n  code-size: 10pt,\n  heading-size-chapter: 16pt,\n  header-mode: \"none\",\n  footer-alignment: center,\n)","title":"Academic Style"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Compact-Layout","page":"Custom Styling","text":"#let config = (\n  text-size: 10pt,\n  code-size: 8pt,\n  table-inset: 6pt,\n  quote-inset: (left: 10pt, right: 10pt, top: 8pt, bottom: 8pt),\n  codeblock-engine: \"builtin\",\n)","title":"Compact Layout"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Advanced-Customization","page":"Custom Styling","text":"","title":"Advanced Customization"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Custom-Document-Content","page":"Custom Styling","text":"The custom.typ file can contain not just configuration, but also document content like custom title pages, prefaces, or dedications. This content will be inserted at the beginning of your document, before the main content.","title":"Custom Document Content"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Custom-Title-Page","page":"Custom Styling","text":"To replace the default title page with your own, set skip-default-titlepage: true in your config:\n\n// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n#let config = (\n  skip-default-titlepage: true,  // Skip the default title page\n  // ... other config\n)\n\n// Your custom title page\n#page(\n  margin: (left: 2cm, right: 2cm, bottom: 3cm, top: 2cm),\n  header: none,\n  footer: none,\n  numbering: none,\n)[\n  #align(center)[\n    #v(3cm)\n    #image(\"logo.png\", width: 150pt)\n    #v(2cm)\n    #text(size: 48pt, weight: \"bold\")[My Amazing Package]\n    #v(1cm)\n    #text(size: 24pt)[Internal Documentation]\n    #v(1fr)\n    #text(size: 14pt, fill: gray)[Confidential • Company Use Only]\n  ]\n]\n\n// Optional: Add your own table of contents\n#outline(depth: 3, indent: true)\n#pagebreak()\n\nImportant: When skip-default-titlepage: true, you are responsible for:\n\nCreating your title page\nAdding the table of contents (if desired) with #outline()\nAdding page breaks (#pagebreak()) as needed","title":"Custom Title Page"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Adding-Preamble-Content","page":"Custom Styling","text":"You can add content before the main documentation without replacing the title page:\n\n// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n#let config = (\n  // ... your config, skip-default-titlepage NOT set\n)\n\n// Content after default title page and TOC, before main content\n// This appears at the start of the main matter (page 1)\n\n#align(center)[\n  #strong[Preface]\n\n  #v(1em)\n\n  This documentation was automatically generated from source code.\n  For the latest version, visit our website.\n]\n\n#pagebreak()","title":"Adding Preamble Content"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Full-Example:-Corporate-Branding","page":"Custom Styling","text":"// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n#let config = (\n  skip-default-titlepage: true,\n  light-blue: rgb(\"0066cc\"),\n  text-font: (\"Helvetica Neue\", \"Arial\"),\n)\n\n// Custom cover page\n#page(\n  margin: 0pt,\n  header: none,\n  footer: none,\n  numbering: none,\n)[\n  // Full-page branded background\n  #rect(\n    width: 100%,\n    height: 100%,\n    fill: gradient.linear(rgb(\"0066cc\"), rgb(\"003d7a\"), angle: 45deg)\n  )[\n    #align(center + horizon)[\n      #text(size: 60pt, fill: white, weight: \"bold\")[ACME Corp]\n      #v(2cm)\n      #text(size: 36pt, fill: white)[Product Documentation]\n      #v(1fr)\n      #text(size: 16pt, fill: white)[Version 2.0 • December 2025]\n    ]\n  ]\n]\n\n// Legal notice page\n#page(\n  header: none,\n  footer: none,\n  numbering: none,\n)[\n  #v(1fr)\n  #align(center)[\n    #text(size: 10pt)[\n      © 2025 ACME Corporation. All rights reserved.\n\n      This document is confidential and proprietary.\n    ]\n  ]\n  #v(1fr)\n]\n\n// Table of contents with custom styling\n#page(numbering: \"i\")[\n  #align(center)[\n    #text(size: 24pt, weight: \"bold\")[Contents]\n  ]\n  #v(2em)\n  #outline(depth: 2, indent: true)\n]\n\n#pagebreak()\n\nThis is useful for:\n\nCorporate documentation: Add branding, confidentiality notices, approval signatures\nAcademic papers: Add author affiliations, abstracts, acknowledgments\nBooks: Add dedications, forewords, prefaces\nInternal docs: Add disclaimers, distribution lists, revision history","title":"Full Example: Corporate Branding"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Custom-Functions","page":"Custom Styling","text":"You can define custom Typst functions:\n\n// docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\n#let config = (\n  // ... your config\n)\n\n// Custom function for highlighted boxes\n#let highlight(body) = {\n  rect(\n    fill: rgb(\"fff3cd\"),\n    stroke: rgb(\"ffc107\") + 1pt,\n    inset: 10pt,\n    radius: 3pt,\n    body\n  )\n}\n\n// Custom header styling\n#let custom-header(body) = {\n  set text(fill: rgb(\"2c3e50\"))\n  strong(body)\n}\n\nNote: When using codeblock-engine: \"custom\", your custom show rule replaces the entire code rendering logic. The codeblock-custom-show function receives the raw content and must handle both block and inline code.","title":"Custom Functions"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Override-Show-Rules","page":"Custom Styling","text":"For less invasive customizations, you can add show rules in custom.typ that work alongside the default rendering:\n\n// Custom link styling (works with any configuration)\n#show link: it => {\n  underline(text(fill: rgb(\"0066cc\"), it))\n}\n\n// Emphasize strong text more\n#show strong: it => {\n  text(fill: rgb(\"c93d39\"), weight: \"bold\", it)\n}\n\nImportant: Show rules added in custom.typ are applied in order. If you're using codeblock-engine: \"custom\", your custom renderer is already a show rule, so additional show raw: rules may conflict.","title":"Override Show Rules"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Complete-Configuration-Reference","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Here's a complete list of all available configuration options with their defaults:\n\n#let config = (\n  // === Colors ===\n  light-blue: rgb(\"6b85dd\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"4266d5\"),\n  light-red: rgb(\"d66661\"),\n  dark-red: rgb(\"c93d39\"),\n  light-green: rgb(\"6bab5b\"),\n  dark-green: rgb(\"3b972e\"),\n  light-purple: rgb(\"aa7dc0\"),\n  dark-purple: rgb(\"945bb0\"),\n  codeblock-background: rgb(\"f6f6f6\"),\n  codeblock-border: rgb(\"e6e6e6\"),\n\n  // === Typography ===\n  text-font: (\"Inter\", \"DejaVu Sans\"),\n  code-font: (\"JetBrains Mono\", \"DejaVu Sans Mono\"),\n  text-size: 11pt,\n  code-size: 9pt,\n  heading-size-title: 24pt,\n  heading-size-part: 18pt,\n  heading-size-chapter: 18pt,\n  heading-size-part-label: 14pt,\n  heading-size-chapter-label: 14pt,\n  heading-size-section: 14pt,\n  heading-size-subsection: 13pt,\n  heading-size-subsubsection: 12pt,\n  admonition-title-size: 12pt,\n  metadata-size: 12pt,\n\n  // === Code Block Customization ===\n  codeblock-engine: \"codly\",         // \"codly\" | \"builtin\" | \"custom\"\n  codeblock-custom-show: none,       // Function: (raw) => { ... }\n  codly-options: (\n    // Empty by default; users can add any codly parameters\n    // Default values are automatically applied:\n    //   languages: codly-languages\n    //   number-format: none\n    //   zebra-fill: none\n    //   fill: cfg.codeblock-background\n    //   stroke: 1pt + cfg.codeblock-border\n  ),\n\n  // === Header Customization ===\n  header-mode: \"chapter\",            // \"chapter\" | \"none\" | \"custom\"\n  header-alignment: right,           // left | center | right\n  header-custom-function: none,      // Function: (loc, cfg) => { ... }\n  header-line-stroke: 0.5pt,\n  header-size: 10pt,\n\n  // === Footer Customization ===\n  footer-mode: \"page-number\",        // \"page-number\" | \"none\" | \"custom\"\n  footer-size: 10pt,\n  footer-alignment: center,          // left | center | right\n  footer-custom-function: none,      // Function: (loc, cfg) => { ... }\n  footer-show-on-part-pages: false,\n\n  // === Page Numbering ===\n  page-numbering-frontmatter: \"i\",   // Roman numerals\n  page-numbering-mainmatter: \"1\",    // Arabic numerals\n  page-numbering-custom: none,       // Function: (nums, cfg) => { ... }\n\n  // === Layout ===\n  outline-number-spacing: 0.5em,\n  outline-indent-step: 1em,\n  outline-part-spacing: 0.5em,\n  outline-filler-spacing: 10pt,\n  outline-line-spacing: -0.2em,\n  table-stroke-width: 0.5pt,\n  table-stroke-color: rgb(\"cccccc\"),\n  table-inset: 8pt,\n  quote-background: rgb(\"f8f8f8\"),\n  quote-border-color: rgb(\"cccccc\"),\n  quote-border-width: 4pt,\n  quote-inset: (left: 15pt, right: 15pt, top: 10pt, bottom: 10pt),\n  quote-radius: (right: 3pt),\n\n  // === Admonitions ===\n  admonition-colors: (\n    default: rgb(\"363636\"),\n    danger: rgb(\"da0b00\"),\n    warning: rgb(\"ffdd57\"),\n    note: rgb(\"209cee\"),\n    info: rgb(\"209cee\"),\n    tip: rgb(\"22c35b\"),\n    compat: rgb(\"1db5c9\"),\n  ),\n  admonition-titles: (\n    default: \"Note\",\n    danger: \"Danger\",\n    warning: \"Warning\",\n    note: \"Note\",\n    info: \"Info\",\n    tip: \"Tip\",\n    compat: \"Compatibility\",\n  ),\n  admonition-title-inset: (left: 1em, right: 5pt, top: 5pt, bottom: 5pt),\n  admonition-title-radius: (top: 5pt),\n  admonition-title-color: white,\n  admonition-content-inset: 10pt,\n  admonition-content-radius: (bottom: 5pt),\n\n  // === Title Page ===\n  skip-default-titlepage: false,\n)","title":"Complete Configuration Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Testing-Your-Style","page":"Custom Styling","text":"","title":"Testing Your Style"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Preview-Quickly","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Use platform=\"none\" for fast iteration:\n\nformat = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\")\n\nThen compile manually:\n\ncd docs/build\ntypst compile YourPackage.typ","title":"Preview Quickly"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Compare-Versions","page":"Custom Styling","text":"# Build with custom styling\njulia docs/make.jl\n\n# Compare with default\nmv docs/build/YourPackage.pdf docs/build/custom.pdf\nrm docs/src/assets/custom.typ\njulia docs/make.jl","title":"Compare Versions"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Font-Installation","page":"Custom Styling","text":"","title":"Font Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Default-Fonts","page":"Custom Styling","text":"DocumenterTypst uses Libertinus Serif (text) and DejaVu Sans Mono (code) by default. These fonts are embedded in Typst packages and work consistently across all platforms without requiring any installation.","title":"Default Fonts"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Using-System-Fonts","page":"Custom Styling","text":"To use system fonts, override the defaults in your custom.typ:\n\n#let config = (\n  text-font: (\"Inter\", \"DejaVu Sans\"),\n  code-font: (\"JetBrains Mono\", \"DejaVu Sans Mono\"),\n)\n\nTypst automatically finds system fonts:\n\nmacOS: All installed fonts\nLinux: Fonts in ~/.fonts and /usr/share/fonts\nWindows: Fonts in C:\\Windows\\Fonts","title":"Using System Fonts"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Custom-Font-Directories","page":"Custom Styling","text":"format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n    platform = \"native\",\n    typst = `typst --font-path /path/to/fonts`\n)","title":"Custom Font Directories"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Embedding-Fonts","page":"Custom Styling","text":"For reproducible builds across platforms:\n\nUse default fonts (Libertinus Serif, DejaVu Sans Mono) - already embedded\nUse Typst_jll (default) - includes basic fonts\nUse Docker - control the entire environment","title":"Embedding Fonts"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Troubleshooting","page":"Custom Styling","text":"","title":"Troubleshooting"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Font-Not-Found","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Problem: \"font not found\" error\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck font is installed: typst fonts (native) or check system fonts\nUse fallback fonts: text-font: (\"PreferredFont\", \"Fallback\", \"DejaVu Sans\")\nSpecify font path: typst --font-path /custom/path\nUse default fonts (no installation needed): text-font: (\"Libertinus Serif\")","title":"Font Not Found"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Colors-Not-Applying","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Problem: Custom colors don't show up\n\nSolutions:\n\nEnsure custom.typ is in docs/src/assets/\nCheck syntax: use rgb(\"rrggbb\") format\nVerify config variable name matches default","title":"Colors Not Applying"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Layout-Issues","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Problem: Spacing or alignment looks wrong\n\nSolutions:\n\nCheck units: use pt, em, % explicitly\nTest with debug output: DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG=1\nCompare with default template","title":"Layout Issues"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Example-Templates","page":"Custom Styling","text":"DocumenterTypst includes a comprehensive example file showing all customization options:\n\nFile location: docs/src/assets/custom.typ.example\n\nThis file contains 10 complete examples demonstrating:\n\nSimple configuration changes (line numbers, zebra stripes)\nUsing builtin Typst rendering (no codly)\nDisabling headers\nCustom header functions\nCustom footers with copyright\nChinese page numbering\nCustom code block renderers\nComprehensive customization combining multiple features\nMinimal header/footer configuration\nDifferent page numbering formats\n\nUsage: Copy this file to docs/src/assets/custom.typ, uncomment the example you want to use, and modify as needed.\n\ncp docs/src/assets/custom.typ.example docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n# Edit custom.typ and uncomment desired example","title":"Example Templates"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Resources","page":"Custom Styling","text":"Typst Documentation\nTypst Guide","title":"Resources"},{"category":"section","location":"manual/styling/#Examples-Gallery","page":"Custom Styling","text":"See Examples for complete styling examples.","title":"Examples Gallery"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Migration-from-LaTeX","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Guide for migrating from Documenter's LaTeX backend to DocumenterTypst.","title":"Migration from LaTeX"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Quick-Migration","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"","title":"Quick Migration"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Step-1:-Update-Dependencies","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"docs/Project.toml - Add DocumenterTypst:\n\n[deps]\nDocumenter = \"e30172f5-a6a5-5a46-863b-614d45cd2de4\"\nDocumenterTypst = \"d7fd56dd-41bc-4b2d-b658-79a5840b2e09\"  # Add this\n\n[compat]\nDocumenter = \"1\"\nDocumenterTypst = \"0.1\"  # Add this","title":"Step 1: Update Dependencies"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Step-2:-Update-make.jl","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Before:\n\nusing Documenter, MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = Documenter.LaTeX(platform = \"native\"),\n    ...\n)\n\nAfter:\n\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst, MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),  # Change this line\n    ...\n)","title":"Step 2: Update make.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Step-3:-Test","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"julia --project=docs -e '\n  using Pkg\n  Pkg.instantiate()\n  include(\"docs/make.jl\")\n'\n\nThat's it! Your markdown files need no changes.","title":"Step 3: Test"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Feature-Mapping","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"","title":"Feature Mapping"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Platform-Options","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"LaTeX Typst Notes\nplatform=\"native\" platform=\"native\" Uses system executable\nplatform=\"tectonic\" platform=\"typst\" Use Typst_jll instead\nN/A platform=\"none\" New: source only","title":"Platform Options"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Math-Syntax","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"LaTeX math just works - no changes needed!\n\n# Works in both backends\n\n`\\\\alpha + \\\\beta = \\\\gamma`\n\n```math\n\\sum_{i=1}^n i = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2}\n```","title":"Math Syntax"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Custom-Styling","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"LaTeX Typst\nCustom .tex templates docs/src/assets/custom.typ\n\\usepackage{...} Typst imports in custom.typ\nLaTeX macros Typst functions","title":"Custom Styling"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#What-Stays-the-Same","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"✅ Markdown files - No changes needed ✅ Math equations - LaTeX syntax supported via mitex ✅ Code blocks - Same syntax highlighting ✅ Cross-references - @ref works identically ✅ Doctests - Full support ✅ Images - Same relative paths ✅ Tables - Same markdown tables ✅ Admonitions - Same !!! note syntax","title":"What Stays the Same"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#What's-Different","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"","title":"What's Different"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Faster-Compilation","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"LaTeX: Several minutes for large docs Typst: < 60 seconds","title":"Faster Compilation"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Better-Error-Messages","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"LaTeX:\n\n! Undefined control sequence.\nl.42 \\mysterycommand\n\nTypst:\n\nerror: unknown variable: mysterycommand\n  ┌─ document.typ:42:2\n  │\n42│ #mysterycommand\n  │  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^","title":"Better Error Messages"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#No-LaTeX-Distribution-Required","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"LaTeX: Install TeXLive/MiKTeX (GB of downloads) Typst: Automatic via Typst_jll (MB of downloads)","title":"No LaTeX Distribution Required"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Breaking-Changes","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"","title":"Breaking Changes"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#None-for-Standard-Usage","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"If you're using standard Documenter features, migration is seamless.","title":"None for Standard Usage"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Rare-Cases","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Custom LaTeX packages: Not supported. Use Typst equivalents in custom.typ.\n\nExample:\n\n% LaTeX (old)\n\\usepackage{tikz}\n\\begin{tikzpicture}\n  ...\n\\end{tikzpicture}\n\n// Typst (new)\n#import \"@preview/cetz:0.1.0\": *\n\n#canvas({\n  ...\n})","title":"Rare Cases"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Migration-Checklist","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"[ ] Add DocumenterTypst to docs/Project.toml\n[ ] Update makedocs() format argument\n[ ] Test build locally\n[ ] Update CI configuration\n[ ] Remove LaTeX-specific dependencies\n[ ] (Optional) Convert custom.tex to custom.typ\n[ ] (Optional) Update documentation to mention new backend","title":"Migration Checklist"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Gradual-Migration","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"You can support both formats temporarily:\n\n# docs/make_latex.jl\nusing Documenter, MyPackage\nmakedocs(format = Documenter.LaTeX(), ...)\n\n# docs/make_typst.jl\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst, MyPackage\nmakedocs(format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(), ...)\n\nCompare outputs before fully switching.","title":"Gradual Migration"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#CI-Migration","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"","title":"CI Migration"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#GitHub-Actions","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Before:\n\n- name: Install LaTeX\n  run: sudo apt-get install texlive-full\n\n- name: Build docs\n  run: julia docs/make.jl\n\nAfter:\n\n# No LaTeX installation needed!\n\n- name: Build docs\n  run: julia docs/make.jl\n\nSimpler and faster!","title":"GitHub Actions"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Troubleshooting-Migration","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"","title":"Troubleshooting Migration"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Issue:-Fonts-Look-Different","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Solution: Typst uses different default fonts. Customize in custom.typ:\n\n#let config = (\n  text-font: (\"Times New Roman\", \"Liberation Serif\"),  // LaTeX-like\n)","title":"Issue: Fonts Look Different"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Issue:-Spacing-Changed","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Solution: Fine-tune in custom.typ:\n\n#let config = (\n  text-size: 11pt,  // Match LaTeX default\n)","title":"Issue: Spacing Changed"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Issue:-Custom-LaTeX-Macros-Missing","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Solution: Rewrite as Typst functions:\n\n// LaTeX: \\newcommand{\\R}{\\mathbb{R}}\n// Typst equivalent ($ is math delimiter in Typst):\n#let R = [ℝ]\n\n// Usage in markdown:\n// @raw typst\n// The set #R represents real numbers.","title":"Issue: Custom LaTeX Macros Missing"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Getting-Help","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"Check Troubleshooting Guide\nSee Advanced Features\nAsk in GitHub Discussions","title":"Getting Help"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Success-Stories","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"\"Migration took 5 minutes, builds are 10x faster!\" - User A \"Finally, no more LaTeX installation issues in CI\" - User B \"The error messages actually make sense now\" - User C","title":"Success Stories"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/migration/#Next-Steps","page":"Migration from LaTeX","text":"After migration:\n\nCustomize styling\nExplore Typst math\nOptimize CI builds","title":"Next Steps"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Advanced-Features","page":"Advanced Features","text":"Advanced usage patterns and examples.","title":"Advanced Features"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Custom-Templates","page":"Advanced Features","text":"","title":"Custom Templates"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Corporate-Branding","page":"Advanced Features","text":"Create docs/src/assets/custom.typ:\n\n#let config = (\n  // Company colors\n  light-blue: rgb(\"0066cc\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"003d7a\"),\n\n  // Company fonts\n  text-font: (\"Helvetica Neue\", \"Arial\"),\n  code-font: (\"Consolas\", \"Courier New\"),\n\n  // Larger text for readability\n  text-size: 12pt,\n  code-size: 10pt,\n)\n\n// Company logo function\n#let company-logo() = {\n  image(\"logo.png\", width: 3cm)\n}","title":"Corporate Branding"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Academic-Style","page":"Advanced Features","text":"#let config = (\n  // Traditional academic styling\n  text-font: (\"Times New Roman\", \"Liberation Serif\"),\n  code-font: (\"Courier New\", \"Liberation Mono\"),\n\n  // Conservative colors\n  light-blue: rgb(\"000080\"),\n  dark-blue: rgb(\"000050\"),\n\n  // Larger line spacing\n  text-size: 12pt,\n)\n\n// Citation helper\n#let cite(key) = {\n  text(fill: rgb(\"0000ff\"))[[#key]]\n}","title":"Academic Style"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Multiple-Output-Formats","page":"Advanced Features","text":"Generate both HTML and PDF:\n\n# docs/make.jl\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst, MyPackage\n\n# Build HTML documentation\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = Documenter.HTML(\n        prettyurls = get(ENV, \"CI\", \"\") == \"true\",\n        canonical = \"https://myorg.github.io/MyPackage.jl\",\n    ),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\ndeploydocs(\n    repo = \"github.com/myorg/MyPackage.jl\",\n    devbranch = \"main\",\n)\n\n# Build PDF documentation\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n        version = get(ENV, \"GITHUB_REF_NAME\", \"dev\"),\n    ),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\n# Upload PDF as artifact in CI\nif get(ENV, \"CI\", \"\") == \"true\"\n    cp(\"docs/build/MyPackage.pdf\", \"MyPackage-$(get(ENV, \"GITHUB_REF_NAME\", \"dev\")).pdf\")\nend","title":"Multiple Output Formats"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Advanced-Math","page":"Advanced Features","text":"","title":"Advanced Math"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Complex-Equations","page":"Advanced Features","text":"```math\n\\begin{align}\n  E &= mc^2 \\\\\n  F &= ma \\\\\n  \\Delta S &\\geq 0\n\\end{align}\n```","title":"Complex Equations"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Custom-Math-Macros","page":"Advanced Features","text":"In custom.typ:\n\n// Define reusable math functions (Note: $ is Typst math delimiter)\n#let bra(x) = [⟨#x|]\n#let ket(x) = [|#x⟩]\n#let braket(x, y) = [⟨#x|#y⟩]","title":"Custom Math Macros"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Performance-Optimization","page":"Advanced Features","text":"","title":"Performance Optimization"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Caching-in-CI","page":"Advanced Features","text":"# .github/workflows/docs.yml\n- name: Cache Julia packages\n  uses: actions/cache@v4\n  with:\n    path: |\n      ~/.julia/packages\n      ~/.julia/artifacts\n    key: julia-pkgs-${{ runner.os }}-${{ hashFiles('docs/Project.toml') }}\n\n- name: Cache Typst fonts\n  uses: actions/cache@v4\n  with:\n    path: ~/.cache/typst\n    key: typst-fonts-${{ runner.os }}","title":"Caching in CI"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Parallel-Builds","page":"Advanced Features","text":"Build multiple versions in parallel:\n\nstrategy:\n  matrix:\n    version: [\"stable\", \"dev\", \"v1.0.0\"]\nsteps:\n  - name: Build ${{ matrix.version }}\n    run: |\n      VERSION=${{ matrix.version }} julia docs/make.jl\n      mv docs/build/Package.pdf Package-${{ matrix.version }}.pdf","title":"Parallel Builds"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Integration-with-Other-Tools","page":"Advanced Features","text":"","title":"Integration with Other Tools"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Pre-commit-Hook","page":"Advanced Features","text":".git/hooks/pre-commit:\n\n#!/bin/bash\n# Build docs before committing\n\njulia --project=docs -e '\n  using Pkg\n  Pkg.instantiate()\n  include(\"docs/make.jl\")\n' || exit 1\n\necho \"Documentation built successfully\"","title":"Pre-commit Hook"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Build-Automation-with-Just","page":"Advanced Features","text":"justfile:\n\n# Build both HTML and PDF documentation\ndocs: docs-html docs-pdf\n\n# Build HTML documentation\ndocs-html:\n    julia --project=docs -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.instantiate(); include(\"docs/make_html.jl\")'\n\n# Build PDF documentation\ndocs-pdf:\n    julia --project=docs -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.instantiate(); include(\"docs/make_pdf.jl\")'\n\n# Clean build artifacts\nclean:\n    julia -e 'rm(\"docs/build\", recursive=true, force=true)'\n\nNote: just is a cross-platform command runner that works on Windows, Linux, and macOS.","title":"Build Automation with Just"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Debugging","page":"Advanced Features","text":"","title":"Debugging"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Inspect-Generated-Typst","page":"Advanced Features","text":"using DocumenterTypst\n\n# Generate source only\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\"),\n    ...\n)\n\n# Manually compile with custom options\nrun(`typst compile docs/build/Package.typ --font-path /custom/fonts`)","title":"Inspect Generated Typst"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Profile-Compilation","page":"Advanced Features","text":"using Profile\n\n@profiler makedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    ...\n)","title":"Profile Compilation"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Migration-Examples","page":"Advanced Features","text":"","title":"Migration Examples"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#From-LaTeX-Backend","page":"Advanced Features","text":"Before (docs/make.jl):\n\nusing Documenter, MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = Documenter.LaTeX(),\n    ...\n)\n\nAfter:\n\nusing Documenter, DocumenterTypst, MyPackage\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    ...\n)\n\nNo changes needed to markdown files!","title":"From LaTeX Backend"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#From-Manual-PDF-Generation","page":"Advanced Features","text":"Before: Complex LaTeX setup with custom templates\n\nAfter: Simple Typst configuration\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    ...\n)\n\nAdd docs/src/assets/custom.typ for styling.","title":"From Manual PDF Generation"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Best-Practices","page":"Advanced Features","text":"Version Control - Track custom.typ in git\nTest Locally - Build before pushing\nUse Caching - Speed up CI builds\nPin Versions - Specify Documenter version in compat\nDocument Changes - Keep CHANGELOG.md updated","title":"Best Practices"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Tips-and-Tricks","page":"Advanced Features","text":"","title":"Tips & Tricks"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Quick-Preview","page":"Advanced Features","text":"# Fast iteration during development\njulia --project=docs -e '\n  using DocumenterTypst\n  makedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(platform = \"none\"),\n    doctest = false,\n  )\n'\ncd docs/build && typst watch Package.typ","title":"Quick Preview"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Conditional-Debugging","page":"Advanced Features","text":"debug_mode = get(ENV, \"DEBUG\", \"false\") == \"true\"\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(\n        platform = debug_mode ? \"none\" : \"typst\"\n    ),\n    ...\n)\n\nif debug_mode\n    ENV[\"DOCUMENTER_TYPST_DEBUG\"] = \"debug\"\nend","title":"Conditional Debugging"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/advanced/#Custom-PDF-Name","page":"Advanced Features","text":"# Generate with custom name\nmakedocs(format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(), ...)\ncp(\"docs/build/Package.pdf\", \"custom-name.pdf\")","title":"Custom PDF Name"},{"category":"section","location":"api/reference/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","text":"DocumenterTypst.jl provides a Documenter.jl plugin for generating documentation in Typst/PDF format.","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"api/reference/#Exported-Types","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Exported Types"},{"category":"section","location":"api/reference/#Internal-Modules","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Internal Modules"},{"category":"section","location":"api/reference/#Usage","page":"API Reference","text":"The main export from DocumenterTypst is the Typst type, which is used as the format argument to makedocs:\n\nusing Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    authors = \"Author Name\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"Guide\" => \"guide.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\nFor detailed configuration options, see the Configuration Guide.","title":"Usage"},{"category":"section","location":"api/reference/#Documenter-Integration","page":"API Reference","text":"DocumenterTypst integrates with Documenter.jl through the format plugin system.\n\nFor complete integration details and all makedocs options, see the Configuration Guide.","title":"Documenter Integration"},{"category":"section","location":"api/reference/#Implementation-Details","page":"API Reference","text":"The package consists of two modules:\n\nDocumenterTypst: The main module (this is what you using)\nDocumenterTypst.TypstWriter: Internal rendering engine\n\nnote: Internal APIs\nThe TypstWriter module is not part of the public API and may change without notice. If you need to extend or customize the Typst rendering, please open an issue to discuss making specific APIs public.","title":"Implementation Details"},{"category":"section","location":"api/reference/#See-Also","page":"API Reference","text":"Documenter.jl Documentation - Main documentation generator\nTypst Documentation - Typst typesetting system\nGetting Started Guide - Quick start guide\nConfiguration Guide - Detailed configuration options","title":"See Also"},{"category":"module","location":"api/reference/#DocumenterTypst.DocumenterTypst","page":"API Reference","text":"DocumenterTypst\n\nA Documenter.jl plugin for generating documentation in Typst/PDF format.\n\nUsage\n\nusing Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\nSee the documentation for DocumenterTypst.Typst for more options.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"DocumenterTypst.DocumenterTypst"},{"category":"type","location":"api/reference/#DocumenterTypst.TypstWriter.Typst","page":"API Reference","text":"DocumenterTypst.Typst(; kwargs...)\n\nOutput format specifier that results in Typst/PDF output. Used together with Documenter.makedocs, e.g.\n\nmakedocs(\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst()\n)\n\nThe makedocs argument sitename will be used for the document title. The authors argument should also be specified and will be used for the document metadata. A version number can be specified with the version option to Typst, which will be printed in the document and also appended to the output PDF file name.\n\nKeyword arguments\n\nplatform sets the platform where the Typst file is compiled. Available options:\n\"typst\" (default): Uses Typst_jll, a Julia binary wrapper that automatically provides the Typst compiler across all platforms.\n\"native\": Uses the system-installed typst executable found in PATH, or a custom path specified via the typst keyword argument.\n\"none\": Skips compilation and only generates the .typ source file in the build directory.\nversion specifies the version number printed on the title page of the manual. Defaults to the value in the TRAVIS_TAG environment variable (although this behaviour is considered deprecated), or to an empty string if TRAVIS_TAG is unset.\ntypst allows specifying a custom path to a typst executable. Only used when platform=\"native\". Can be either a String path or a Cmd object.\noptimize_pdf enables automatic PDF optimization using pdfcpu after compilation. Defaults to true. When enabled, reduces PDF file size by 60-85% by compressing uncompressed streams and optimizing PDF structure. Set to false to skip optimization (e.g., for faster builds during development).\nuse_system_fonts controls whether to allow Typst to use system fonts. Defaults to true. Setting to false will possibly decrease the size of the PDF file.\nfont_paths specifies custom font directories for Typst to search. Defaults to String[] (empty). Provide a vector of directory paths to add custom fonts. Each path will be passed to Typst as --font-path argument.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"DocumenterTypst.TypstWriter.Typst"},{"category":"module","location":"api/reference/#DocumenterTypst.TypstWriter","page":"API Reference","text":"A module for rendering Document objects to Typst and PDF.\n\nKeywords\n\nTypstWriter uses the following additional keyword arguments that can be passed to Documenter.makedocs: authors, sitename.\n\nsitename is the site's title displayed in the title bar and at the top of the navigation menu. It goes into the Typst document title.\n\nauthors can be used to specify the authors. It goes into the Typst document metadata.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"DocumenterTypst.TypstWriter"},{"category":"section","location":"#DocumenterTypst.jl","page":"Home","text":"Fast, modern PDF generation for Julia documentation.\n\nDocumenterTypst.jl is a Documenter.jl plugin that generates high-quality PDF documentation using the Typst typesetting system.","title":"DocumenterTypst.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Why-DocumenterTypst?","page":"Home","text":"","title":"Why DocumenterTypst?"},{"category":"section","location":"#Lightning-Fast","page":"Home","text":"< 60 seconds to compile the full Julia documentation (vs several minutes with LaTeX)\nPowered by Typst's incremental compilation engine","title":"⚡ Lightning Fast"},{"category":"section","location":"#Beautiful-Output","page":"Home","text":"Modern, professional typography\nConsistent styling across all platforms\nHigh-quality PDF output optimized for both screen and print","title":"🎨 Beautiful Output"},{"category":"section","location":"#Easy-Setup","page":"Home","text":"No LaTeX distribution required\nWorks out of the box with Typst_jll.jl\nCross-platform support (Linux, macOS, Windows)","title":"🔧 Easy Setup"},{"category":"section","location":"#Flexible-Math-Support","page":"Home","text":"LaTeX math via mitex for backward compatibility\nNative Typst math for new projects\nSeamless integration with existing Documenter documentation","title":"🧮 Flexible Math Support"},{"category":"section","location":"#Production-Ready","page":"Home","text":"Built on stable Documenter internal APIs (same as DocumenterVitepress)\nComprehensive test coverage (133+ tests)\nActive maintenance and community support","title":"🎯 Production Ready"},{"category":"section","location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","text":"using Documenter\nusing DocumenterTypst\n\nmakedocs(\n    sitename = \"MyPackage\",\n    authors = \"Your Name\",\n    format = DocumenterTypst.Typst(),\n    pages = [\n        \"Home\" => \"index.md\",\n        \"API\" => \"api.md\",\n    ]\n)\n\nThis generates a professional PDF with table of contents, cross-references, syntax highlighting, and more.\n\nOutput: docs/build/MyPackage.pdf\n\nSee Getting Started for detailed instructions.","title":"Quick Start"},{"category":"section","location":"#Features","page":"Home","text":"Feature Status\nFast Compilation ✅\nLaTeX Math ✅\nTypst Math ✅\nCode Blocks ✅\nTables ✅\nImages ✅\nCross-References ✅\nAdmonitions ✅\nFootnotes ✅\nTable of Contents ✅\nCustom Templates ✅\nMulti-page Docs ✅","title":"Features"},{"category":"section","location":"#Comparison-with-LaTeX-Backend","page":"Home","text":" DocumenterTypst Documenter (LaTeX)\nCompilation Time < 60s (Julia docs) Several minutes\nSetup Zero-config Requires LaTeX distribution\nFile Size Compact Compact\nOutput Quality High High\nMath Support LaTeX + Typst LaTeX only\nError Messages Clear and helpful Sometimes cryptic\nIncremental Builds ✅ Fast ❌ Slow","title":"Comparison with LaTeX Backend"},{"category":"section","location":"#Documentation","page":"Home","text":"Pages = [\n    \"manual/getting_started.md\",\n    \"manual/configuration.md\",\n    \"manual/math.md\",\n    \"manual/styling.md\",\n]\nDepth = 1","title":"Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"DocumenterTypst\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Community","page":"Home","text":"GitHub: lucifer1004/DocumenterTypst.jl\nIssues: Report bugs or request features\nDiscussions: Share your experience and ask questions","title":"Community"},{"category":"section","location":"#Acknowledgments","page":"Home","text":"DocumenterTypst.jl builds upon:\n\nDocumenter.jl - The Julia documentation generator\nTypst - Modern typesetting system\nmitex - LaTeX math in Typst\nDocumenterVitepress.jl - Inspiration for the plugin architecture","title":"Acknowledgments"},{"category":"section","location":"#License","page":"Home","text":"MIT License. See LICENSE for details.","title":"License"}]
}
